- Rejection of the Greatest Hits Collection: although it shares some technical strengths (warm analog tone, preserved micro‑dynamics, tasteful remastering), its greatest‑hits nature and emphasis on intimate, forward lead vocals plus multi‑tracked harmonies conflict with two important dislikes: a tendency toward radio‑polished, harmony‑stacked fronts and non‑cohesive sequencing. Those traits dilute the raw, riff‑forward, gravelly‑fronted hard‑rock character I favor. In short, the Greatest Hits offers some attractive mastering choices but likely fails to deliver the consistent band‑sequenced, live‑immediacy, riff‑driven album experience that defines my preference, so I reject it in favor of the cohesive artist album.

